            . I live in Northampton-square. I was a customer of Mr. Wells's. I paid the prisoner 6 1/4 d. myself. I saw Mr. Wells three days after, and told him I had paid his servant.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-212-person2014">
                  GEORGE 
                  WELLS
               <interp inst="t18200412-212-person2014" type="surname" value="WELLS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-212-person2014" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-212-person2014" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. It was the duty of the prisoner to account to me for the money he had received, but he never did. He left me on the 21st of February, and left this letter (read) -</p>
               <p>"My reasons for leaving you I dare not say, I have no fault to find - what money I owe you I will call and pay. I am obliged to fly for reasons. I have no doubt you will think harsh of me, and it will go as hard with me for so doing, but I dare not tell the reason."</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had not drawn my wages of my master; I was going to receive my prize-money to make the deficiency good.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-212-verdict1234" type="verdictDescription">
